    "description_long": "This object is a decorative water feature resembling a two-tiered wooden barrel fountain. The lower and upper barrels are bound with black metal bands and have a natural wood texture. Water flows from a black cylindrical spout at the top, cascading down a vertical channel cut into the upper barrel and into the lower basin, which contains small rocks and green plants for added detail. The water appears to be animated or stylized, with a blue, semi-transparent look. Several thin rods or pipes protrude from the top, possibly for structural or decorative purposes. The overall design is rustic and would fit well in parks, gardens, or urban relaxation areas.",
